
The files included in the tarball are,
C source files for an embedded application that builds and runs (with no errors or warnings) on an embedded system,
A Makefile to build and test my application, which takes options including:
	default ... build my program (compiling with the -Wall and -Wextra options).
	check ... execute an automated smoke-test of my application to see if it runs and can talk to its sensors/actuators.
	clean ... delete all programs and output generated by the Makefile
	dist ... (runnable on a Linux desktop or server) create the deliverable tarball,
test.sh, including all the tests that will be run by the check option of the makefile,
a README file containing: the descriptions of each of the included files as well as any other comments on my submission that I would like to bring to your attention (e.g., research, limitations, features, testing methodology).